  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BERMUTU-Better Education through Reformed Management and Universal Teacher Upgrading</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The development objective is to contribute to the improvement of the overall quality and performance of teachers through enhancing teachers&apos; knowledge of subject matter and pedagogical skills in the classroom. Improvement of teacher quality and performance is to be measured by: (i) the increased number of teachers meeting academic qualifications mandated by the Teacher Law; (ii) the increased number of primary and junior secondary teachers in BERMUTU Districts using classroom instruction with specific subject and age appropriate pedagogy; and (iii) the reduction in absenteeism of teachers in BERMUTU Districts.</narrative>
  </description>
